      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study performed with at least three mesh refinement levels; discretization error estimated and shown to be within acceptable bounds for hemolysis index prediction.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed (coarse: 2.1M, medium: 6.8M, fine: 18.4M cells). Richardson extrapolation yielded a discretization error of 3.2% on the hemolysis index at the medium mesh level, which is acceptable for MRL 2 comparative analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
